# Speculate bubble: window 3, the MIDDLE run (bob, lane position 1) goes
# red. Ports docs/plans/phase5.md §5.2's speculate_bubble row, UPDATED for
# the phase-5 review's F2 ruling (Zuul reset semantics): a red at lane index
# i>0 is tested against a PREDICTED base (a predecessor's own chainTip, not
# the real target tip) — its predecessor might be the one actually at fault
# — so only lane index 0 (proven against reality) parks on red. Bob at index
# 1 instead Skips WITHOUT parking and re-queues; carol (behind him) also
# Skips unparked via the usual suffix invalidation; alice (ahead of bob) is
# untouched and keeps running toward landing.
#
# This file used to assert bob parked (Rejected) right here, at lane index
# 1, with alice still in flight ahead of him — exactly the false-negative
# park F2 fixes: bob's red was never actually proven against the real target
# tip at that point, only against alice's still-unlanded, predicted
# chainTip. The scenario below now runs the story all the way through: bob
# re-queues, retests once he's genuinely at lane index 0 (alice having
# landed and the window rebuilt from the real tip), and THEN — only once
# proven red against reality — parks for real.

set-mode main speculate 3
direct-push main files/spec

push-candidate main alice a files/a
push-candidate main bob b files/b
push-candidate main carol c files/c
tick                                # window fills: alice(#0)->bob(#1)->carol(#2)

assert-pipeline-depth main 3
await-started test
await-started '@#1' test
await-started '@#2' test

release-check '@#1' test failed       # bob (middle, predicted base) goes red: bubble, unparked

assert-event skipped
! assert-event rejected                 # not proven against reality yet: no park
assert-slot-parked-none main bob b       # Skipped, NOT parked: free to re-queue
assert-slot-parked-none main carol c     # Skipped, NOT parked: free to re-queue
assert-pipeline-depth main 1             # only alice's run survives
! assert-slot-gone main alice a          # alice hasn't landed yet

release-check test passed           # alice's own check finally goes green: lands
assert-landed-order main a
assert-slot-gone main alice a

tick                                 # next refill: lane was empty, so bob re-forms at INDEX 0 —
                                      # against the real (now-advanced) target tip, not a prediction
assert-pipeline-depth main 2         # bob(#0, real base) -> carol(#1, predicted on bob)
await-started test                   # bob
await-started '@#1' test             # carol, chained onto bob's predicted chainTip

release-check test failed            # bob is NOW at lane index 0: red here IS proven against
                                      # reality, so THIS time it parks for real
assert-event rejected
assert-slot-parked main bob b        # real park: proven red against the actual target tip
assert-slot-parked-none main carol c # carol bubbles again, still not her fault
assert-pipeline-depth main 0

tick                                  # carol re-queues alone; bob stays parked
assert-pipeline-depth main 1
await-started test
release-check test passed
assert-landed-order main a c
assert-slot-gone main carol c

-- files/spec/.gauntlet.kdl --
check "test" {
    command "true"
}
-- files/a/a.txt --
a
-- files/b/b.txt --
b
-- files/c/c.txt --
c
